name: Numpad
comment:
Library for working with a numpad.

@docs numpad

values.name: numpad
values.comment:
A signal of records indicating the directionality of which number is pressed.
  * `{ x =-1, y = 1 }`: 7 (up-left)
  * `{ x = 0, y = 1 }`: 8 (up)
  * `{ x = 1, y = 1 }`: 9 (up-right)
  * `{ x =-1, y = 0 }`: 6 (left)
  * `{ x = 0, y = 0 }`: 5 (center)
  * `{ x = 0, y = 1 }`: 4 (right)
  * `{ x =-1, y =-1 }`: 1 (down-left)
  * `{ x = 0, y =-1 }`: 2 (down)
  * `{ x = 1, y =-1 }`: 3 (down-right)
